<section>
    <div class='container'>
    <div class="check-switch-wrapper">
        <div class="left-side-items">
            {% for block in section.blocks %}
                <div class="item {{ block.settings.color | replace: ' ', '-' | downcase }}">
                    <img src="{{ block.settings.image | img_url: 'master' }}" alt="{{ block.settings.title }}">
                    <h2>{{ block.settings.title }}</h2>
                </div>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>

        <div class="right-side-filter">
            <h2>Just hover <br><strong style="color:#EDD146">over it!</strong></h2>
            <div class="filterGroup">
                <div id="colorFilter">
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="red-switches" checked> Red Switches</label>
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="blue-switches"> Blue Switches</label>
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="green-switches"> Green Switches</label>
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="white-switches"> White Switches</label>
                  </div>

                  <div id="colorFilter">
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="yellow-switches"> Yellow Switches</label>
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="brown-switches"> Brown Switches</label>
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="purple-switches"> Purple Switches</label>
                    <label><input type="radio" name="color" value="black-switches"> Black Switches</label>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="content-hover-blocks text" style="display: none;">
                  <div class="item red-switches">
                      <h3>🔴 Red Switches – Light & Fast</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Linear<br>
                          Feedback: Smooth, no tactile bump<br>
                          Noise Level: Silent<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~45g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Fast-paced gaming<br>
                          - Users who prefer effortless keystrokes<br>
                          - Quiet environments<br>
                          Examples: Cherry MX Red, Gateron Red, Akko Red.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Red switches are designed for speed and efficiency. They require minimal force to press, making them a favorite among gamers who need quick responses. Their smooth actuation also makes them great for long typing sessions without causing fatigue.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item blue-switches">
                      <h3>🔵 Blue Switches – Clicky & Satisfying</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Clicky<br>
                          Feedback: Noticeable tactile bump with an audible click<br>
                          Noise Level: Loud<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~50g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Typists who enjoy audible feedback<br>
                          - Writers and programmers<br>
                          - Users who prefer a classic mechanical feel<br>
                          Examples: Cherry MX Blue, Gateron Blue, Akko Blue.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Blue switches are known for their loud and clicky keystrokes, making them a favorite among typists. The pronounced tactile bump provides clear feedback, ensuring each keypress is deliberate. However, their noise level may not be suitable for shared or quiet environments.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item green-switches">
                      <h3>🟢 Green Switches – Heavy & Clicky</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Clicky<br>
                          Feedback: Strong tactile bump with a loud click<br>
                          Noise Level: Very Loud<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~80g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Users who love strong resistance and feedback<br>
                          - Typists who prefer a firm keypress<br>
                          - Classic mechanical keyboard enthusiasts<br>
                          Examples: Cherry MX Green, Gateron Green, Akko Green.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Green switches are similar to blue switches but require more force to actuate, making them the heaviest clicky option. They provide a crisp, satisfying click with a pronounced bump, perfect for those who enjoy deliberate, forceful keystrokes.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item white-switches">
                      <h3>⚪ White Switches – Soft & Silent</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Linear or Tactile (depends on the manufacturer)<br>
                          Feedback: Smooth or subtle bump<br>
                          Noise Level: Silent or very quiet<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~35g - 50g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Users who prefer quiet typing<br>
                          - Office environments and shared spaces<br>
                          - Fast and effortless keystrokes<br>
                          Examples: Gateron Silent White, Akko CS White, Kailh BOX White.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          White switches are known for their soft and silent actuation. Some models, like Gateron Silent White, are fully linear with smooth keystrokes, while others, like Kailh BOX White, have a light click and tactile feedback. They are an excellent choice for users who want a quiet yet responsive typing experience.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item yellow-switches">
                      <h3>🟡 Yellow Switches – Smooth & Speedy</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Linear<br>
                          Feedback: Smooth, no tactile bump<br>
                          Noise Level: Quiet<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~50g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Gamers who want a fast response<br>
                          - Users who prefer silent but smooth keystrokes<br>
                          - Long typing sessions<br>
                          Examples: Gateron Yellow, Akko CS Yellow.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Yellow switches are a middle ground between reds and blacks. They offer a smooth keystroke with slightly higher actuation force than reds, making them ideal for gaming and typing.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item brown-switches">
                      <h3>🟤 Brown Switches – Balanced & Versatile</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Tactile<br>
                          Feedback: Gentle tactile bump<br>
                          Noise Level: Medium<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~55g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Office workers<br>
                          - Gamers who want feedback without loud clicks<br>
                          - All-purpose typing<br>
                          Examples: Cherry MX Brown, Gateron Brown, Akko Brown.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Brown switches are a hybrid between linear and clicky switches, offering a tactile bump without a loud click. They are great for users who want feedback without excessive noise.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item purple-switches">
                      <h3>🟣 Purple Switches – Tactile & Silent</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Tactile<br>
                          Feedback: Strong tactile bump<br>
                          Noise Level: Quiet<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~50g - 60g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Users who want tactile feedback but prefer silence<br>
                          - Office and workspaces<br>
                          Examples: Akko CS Lavender Purple, Kailh Pro Purple.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Purple switches offer a pronounced tactile bump but without the clicky sound of blue or green switches. They are ideal for typists and office workers.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="item black-switches">
                      <h3>⚫ Black Switches – Heavy & Precise</h3>
                      <div class="text-hover-blocks">
                          <p>🔹 Specifications:<br>
                          Type: Linear<br>
                          Feedback: Smooth, no tactile bump<br>
                          Noise Level: Silent<br>
                          Actuation Force: ~60g</p>

                          <p>🔹 Best for:<br>
                          - Gamers who want high precision<br>
                          - Typists who prefer a firm press<br>
                          - Users who dislike accidental keypresses<br>
                          Examples: Cherry MX Black, Gateron Black, Akko CS Black.</p>

                          <p>🔹 Description:<br>
                          Black switches are similar to reds but require more force to actuate. This prevents accidental keypresses, making them a great choice for gamers and precise typists.</p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <p class='when-selected-all'>
                  <strong>Mechanical Keyboard Switches Overview</strong>  

                  Mechanical keyboard switches are the core components that determine the feel, sound, and responsiveness of each keystroke. Unlike membrane keyboards, mechanical switches use individual mechanisms for each key, providing better durability and a more satisfying typing experience.  
                  
                  There are three main types of mechanical switches:  
                  
                  - Clicky – Produces a tactile bump with an audible click. Ideal for typists who enjoy feedback.  
                  - Tactile – Offers a noticeable bump without the loud click, making them great for both typing and gaming.  
                  - Linear – Smooth and quiet with no tactile bump, providing fast actuation, preferred by gamers.  
                  
                  Switches also come in various colors, each indicating different characteristics such as actuation force, noise level, and responsiveness. Popular brands include **Cherry MX, Gateron, Kailh, and Akko**, with colors like **Blue, Red, Brown, Black, Silver, and more**.  
                  
                  Choosing the right switch depends on personal preference, whether for gaming, office work, or general use. 🚀
                </p>
            </div>
    </div>
    </div>
</section>

<script>
    document.querySelectorAll('#colorFilter input').forEach(function(radio) {
        radio.addEventListener('change', function(event) {
            var selectedColor = event.target.value;
            var switchItems = document.querySelectorAll('.left-side-items .item');
            var hoverBlocks = document.querySelectorAll('.content-hover-blocks .item');
            var tableSwitches = document.querySelector('.table-switches');
            var descriptionText = document.querySelector('.when-selected-all');

            if (selectedColor === 'all') {
                document.querySelector('.content-hover-blocks').style.display = 'none';
                switchItems.forEach(item => item.style.display = 'flex'); 
                hoverBlocks.forEach(item => item.style.display = 'none');
                descriptionText.style.display = 'block'; // Показываем описание
            } else {
                document.querySelector('.content-hover-blocks').style.display = 'block';
                descriptionText.style.display = 'none'; // Скрываем описание
                
                switchItems.forEach(item => {
                    if (item.classList.contains(selectedColor)) {
                        item.style.display = 'flex';
                    } else {
                        item.style.display = 'none';
                    }
                });
                
                hoverBlocks.forEach(item => {
                    if (item.classList.contains(selectedColor)) {
                        item.style.display = 'block';
                    } else {
                        item.style.display = 'none';
                    }
                });
            }
        });
    });
</script>


